# Git And Branching Rules

- Use commit messages in the format `type(scope): description`.
- Keep descriptions lowercase, specific, and focused on the change.
- Use branch names in the format `type/short-description`.
- Use short, hyphenated branch names such as `feat/add-to-cart-button`.
- Use PR titles in the same format as commit messages: `type(scope): description`.
- Keep the `type` consistent across the branch name, commit message, and PR title when possible.

## Commit Message Format

Use format: `type(scope): description`

Example: `feat(cart): add add-to-cart button`

## Branch Naming Convention

Use format: `type/short-description`

Example: `feat/add-to-cart-button`

## PR Naming

Use the same format as commit messages: `type(scope): description`

Example: `feat(cart): add add-to-cart button`

Common `type` values:
- `feat`
- `fix`
- `chore`
- `docs`
- `refactor`
- `test`
